job as soon
as possible.

20:25.658 --> 20:30.496 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: Although there are
no hard statistics
on how many refugees do or don't
find jobs

20:30.529 --> 20:37.470 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
after their aid ends, some
qualify for public
assistance. Ibrahim Rosic was
literally torn

20:37.503 --> 20:39.505 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
apart in the Bosnian conflict.

20:39.538 --> 20:51.117 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
IBRAHIM ROSIC: In 1994 I stepped
on a land
mine. I lost my left leg, and my
right leg

20:51.150 --> 20:55.354 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was severely damaged. I have no
knee. I can't
bend it.

20:55.387 --> 21:00.025 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: He is officially
100 percent
disabled, but, says the former
engineer:

21:00.059 --> 21:05.331 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
IBRAHIM ROSIC: I work two jobs.
I work full-time
as a director at Mohawk Valley
Community College,

21:05.364 --> 21:11.537 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and I also work as an adjunct
instructor at
SUNY Poly. I am not a burden on
the community.

21:11.570 --> 21:19.078 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I am not a burden on social
services. Yes,
community helped me to get this,
but now it's

21:19.111 --> 21:23.616 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
my time to pay back. And I would
say most
refugees do the same.

21:23.649 --> 21:29.555 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: So, are refugees
the economic
boon that motivated immigrants
famously have

21:29.588 --> 21:30.823 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
been?

21:30.856 --> 21:34.093 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Yes, says economist Jeffrey
Sachs, but there
are negatives.

21:34.126 --> 21:38.164 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY SACHS, Columbia
University: Some workers
face increased job competition
and their wages

21:38.197 --> 21:44.970 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
can be driven down. If
lower-skilled immigrants
come, then lower-skilled
American workers

21:45.004 --> 21:52.044 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
may see a decline in their
wages, whereas
business owners may see more
workers at lower

21:52.077 --> 21:53.779 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
cost for them.

21:53.812 --> 21:59.818 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: And what if, as
many Americans
fear, even just a few are
terrorists?

21:59.852 --> 22:02.788 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Shelly Callahan's response? This
isn't Europe.

22:02.821 --> 22:10.329 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHELLY CALLAHAN: Refugees are
the most intensively
screened immigrants really to
come to this

22:10.362 --> 22:17.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
country, about two years of
intense scrutiny
by the Department of Homeland
Security, the

22:17.169 --> 22:23.142 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FBI, ICE, Department of State.
There's DNA
testing involved.

22:23.175 --> 22:27.580 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
YOUSIF AL SAAD, Iraq War
Refugee: For those
people who is proven as bad
people, we don't

22:27.613 --> 22:29.381 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
want them here.

22:29.415 --> 22:34.253 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: The Al Saad family,
Palestinians
who for decades lived in
Baghdad, fled during

22:34.286 --> 22:38.657 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the troop surge of 2007, the
deadliest year
of the Iraq War.

22:38.691 --> 22:42.861 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
YOUSIF AL SAAD: I got kidnapped
there by,
I don't know, some militia.

22:42.895 --> 22:44.730 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOMAN: One of my other brothers,
too.

22:44.763 --> 22:45.798 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
YOUSIF AL SAAD: My other
brother.

22:45.831 --> 22:47.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
WOMAN: They beat him up.

22:47.099 --> 22:49.101 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
YOUSIF AL SAAD: He got beat up.
I lost many
friends of mine.

22:49.134 --> 22:53.672 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: They spent three
years in a camp
on the Syrian border, before
being cleared

22:53.706 --> 22:55.975 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
for transit to the United
States.

22:56.008 --> 23:03.215 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Yousif Al Saad went to work at
the Chobani
yogurt plant outside Utica,
whose CEO, Hamdi

23:03.249 --> 23:09.822 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Ulukaya, has championed the
rights of refugees
and hired hundreds of them. We
were supposed

23:09.855 --> 23:15.427 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to tape there, but at the last
minute, Chobani
pulled out, citing security
concerns, fear

23:15.461 --> 23:18.964 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for the safety of employees in
the current
political environment.

23:18.998 --> 23:24.770 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHELLY CALLAHAN: Well, I think
that is probably
reflective of the very sad
climate in this

23:24.803 --> 23:30.075 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
country with regard to politics
at the moment
and rhetoric.

23:30.109 --> 23:33.345 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MEN AND WOMEN: With liberty and
justice for
all.

23:33.379 --> 23:36.348 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN: Let's have a round of
applause for our
new citizens.

23:36.382 --> 23:38.183 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(APPLAUSE)

23:38.217 --> 23:44.657 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: A few weeks ago in
Utica, Yousif
Al Saad joined 29 others, from
15 different

23:44.690 --> 23:47.559 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
countries in becoming a U.S.
citizen.

23:47.593 --> 23:49.528 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOMAN: Congratulations. Your new
flag.

23:49.561 --> 23:52.331 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: Almost all were
refugees.

23:52.364 --> 23:56.001 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We leave the last word to Judge
David Peebles.

23:56.035 --> 23:59.972 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDGE DAVID PEEBLES, New York:
America is
now your country. I cannot
overemphasize the

24:00.005 --> 24:04.777 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
need now, more than ever, for
you and your
fellow citizens to unite, answer
the call

24:04.810 --> 24:09.481 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and assist in bettering our
society and our
world. Congratulations on
becoming a citizen

24:09.515 --> 24:14.353 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of the greatest nation on earth.
God bless
all of you and God bless
America.

24:14.386 --> 24:16.021 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(APPLAUSE)

24:16.055 --> 24:23.929 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL SOLMAN: For the "PBS
NewsHour," this
is economics correspondent Paul
Solman.

24:23.962 --> 24:35.240 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Stay with us.

24:35.274 --> 24:40.946 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour": a
new movie about
Anita Hill's sexual harassment
charges against

24:40.979 --> 24:47.853 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Justice Clarence Thomas; the
harsh conditions
facing India's rural work force;
and model

24:47.886 --> 24:52.491 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Padma Lakshmi on using her fame
to do good.

24:52.524 --> 24:58.530 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, first, the grinding war in
Yemen has
further broken an already
failing state. Now

24:58.564 --> 25:03.902 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
there are new questions about
the depth of
U.S. involvement there, aiding
what has become

25:03.936 --> 25:07.172 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
a proxy war.

25:07.206 --> 25:13.479 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Saudi Arabia and its Sunni
allies launched
the air campaign 13 months ago,
aimed at Shiite

25:13.512 --> 25:19.785 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Houthi rebels in league with
Iran. But the
United Nations estimates the
airstrikes account

25:19.818 --> 25:28.460 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for 60 percent of the 3,200
civilians killed
in the conflict so far.

25:28.494 --> 25:32.364 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Just last month, an air raid on
a crowded
market left 119 people dead.

25:32.398 --> 25:34.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RUPERT COLVILLE, Spokesman,
United Nations
High Commissioner for Human
Rights: Despite

25:34.466 --> 25:41.173 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
public promises to investigate
such incidents,
we have yet to see progress in
any such investigations.

25:41.206 --> 25:47.880 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now Human Rights
Watch says
its investigators visited the
site, and determined

25:47.913 --> 25:54.520 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the strikes used U.S.-supplied
bombs. The
group said it illustrates --
quote -- "tragically,

25:54.553 --> 25:58.424 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
why countries should stop
selling arms to
Saudi Arabia."

25:58.457 --> 26:04.596 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In response, the U.S. Central
Command said:
"Selection and final vetting of
targets in

26:04.630 --> 26:10.335 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the campaign are made by the
Saudi-led coalition,
not the United States."

26:10.369 --> 26:16.008 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Secretary of State John Kerry
said he didn't
have any -- quote -- "solid
information" about

26:16.041 --> 26:23.248 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
what weapons were used. He spoke
during a
visit to Bahrain, a member of
the Saudi coalition.

26:23.282 --> 26:31.290 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The U.S. aids that coalition,
and in November
approved a nearly $1.3 billion
rearming program

26:31.323 --> 26:39.698 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for the Saudis. "Foreign Policy"
magazine
reports that there have been
roughly 750 U.S.

26:39.731 --> 26:42.968 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
aerial refueling missions.

26:43.001 --> 26:49.775 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, a cease-fire is
scheduled to begin
Sunday, with new peace talks
scheduled for

26:49.808 --> 26:51.810 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
April 18.

26:51.844 --> 26:56.815 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For more on the conflict and the
U.S. role
in Yemen, I'm joined now by
retired Army Colonel

26:56.849 --> 27:02.621 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Derek Harvey. He was an
intelligence officer
and special adviser to the
commander of U.S.

27:02.654 --> 27:05.591 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
forces in Iraq, General David
Petraeus.

27:05.624 --> 27:08.894 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Colonel Harvey, thank you for
being with us
again.

27:08.927 --> 27:14.032 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This report by Human Rights
Watch is disturbing,
but hasn't it been known for
some time that

27:14.066 --> 27:18.003 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
there have been large numbers of
civilian
casualties in this war?

27:18.036 --> 27:21.907 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
COL. DEREK HARVEY (RET.), U.S.
Army: Yes,
it's been true that large
numbers of civilian

27:21.940 --> 27:23.709 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
casualties.

27:23.742 --> 27:29.348 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think it's inevitable,
given the skill
and lack of training and use of
the weapons

27:29.381 --> 27:33.418 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and technology that the Saudi
air forces employ
in Yemen today.

27:33.452 --> 27:38.357 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And what do you
mean by that?
What do you mean by lack of
training and skill,

27:38.390 --> 27:40.092 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
or lack of skill?

27:40.125 --> 27:43.762 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
COL. DEREK HARVEY: Well, Judy, I
think we
are very accustomed in America
and elsewhere

27:43.795 --> 27:49.234 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
in the world to the high
professionalism and
great skill of the U.S. Air
Force and Western

27:49.268 --> 27:55.407 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
European countries, who have
rules of engagement,
training, and capabilities that
allow them

27:55.440 --> 27:59.344 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to reduce collateral damage and
civilian casualties.

27:59.378 --> 28:03.749 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Other countries around the
world, to include
the Saudi Arabian air force,
doesn't have

28:03.782 --> 28:09.888 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that same level of skill. They
fly higher.
They're not as good at employing
those weapons.

28:09.922 --> 28:15.694 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They, you know, are probably
trying to avoid
civilian casualties. Everything
we see seems

28:15.727 --> 28:20.899 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to suggest that. But it's
inevitable, given
the type of conflict and the
skill level of

28:20.933 --> 28:22.734 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
those that are involved in this
conflict.

28:22.768 --> 28:28.106 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Why did the U.S.,
why did this
administration decide to provide
this kind

28:28.140 --> 28:33.679 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of military support to the
Saudis and to this
coalition, intelligence,
refueling, and all

28:33.712 --> 28:35.480 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the rest?

28:35.514 --> 28:39.885 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
COL. DEREK HARVEY: Well, part of
it is, we
have been attempting to bolster
the relationship

28:39.918 --> 28:46.892 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with Saudi Arabia after some of
the fractious
disagreement about the Iran
nuclear deal,

28:46.925 --> 28:52.831 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and concerns in Saudi Arabia and
in the Gulf
about Iranian continued efforts
to encroach

28:52.864 --> 28:55.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
on Sunni Arab areas.

28:55.534 --> 29:02.207 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And with the successes of Iran
in Iraq and
in Syria and Lebanon, they saw
this as another

29:02.241 --> 29:07.446 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
threat from Iran supporting the
Shia-aligned
Houthis in Yemen that was going
to threaten

29:07.479 --> 29:13.785 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Saudi Arabia. The United States
simply decided
it was best to pollster and
repair that relationship

29:13.819 --> 29:17.556 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with Riyadh and support them in
the way that
we have been doing it.

29:17.589 --> 29:21.159 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And what -- I
mean, can you
spell out a little bit more
about what the

29:21.193 --> 29:22.995 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
support entails?

29:23.028 --> 29:28.700 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
COL. DEREK HARVEY: Clearly, we
are providing
some advice and assistance with
limited what

29:28.734 --> 29:34.473 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I would call coaching. But we're
not selecting
or directing the operations or
directing any

29:34.506 --> 29:36.341 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
targeting.

29:36.375 --> 29:40.012 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There is intelligence that's
being provided
from a range of U.S.
intelligence capabilities,

29:40.045 --> 29:45.484 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to include drones that are
flying over Yemen
on a regular basis. The air
refueling that

29:45.517 --> 29:50.522 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was commented on in the intro
piece is -- has
been an important element.

29:50.555 --> 29:56.428 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, mostly, the Saudi Arabians
and the other
Gulf countries that are involved
in this conflict

29:56.461 --> 30:03.268 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
primarily use U.S. weapons and
munitions.
And, inevitably, it's going to
be American-sourced

30:03.301 --> 30:07.005 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
equipment, weapons and munitions
that will
be used in Yemen.

30:07.039 --> 30:11.743 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, how much
responsibility
does the United States bear for
these civilian

30:11.777 --> 30:13.545 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
casualties?

30:13.578 --> 30:19.551 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
COL. DEREK HARVEY: Well, I don't
think we're
involved in selecting any of
those targets.

30:19.584 --> 30:21.386 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It's indirect.

30:21.420 --> 30:27.793 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have been supporting an ally,
and, in that
sense, you know, there is some
responsibility.

30:27.826 --> 30:31.763 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The United States
administration, the Obama
administration, Secretary Kerry
and others,

30:31.797 --> 30:38.303 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
have distanced themselves very
clearly from
that conflict and are
recognizing that it's

30:38.336 --> 30:41.907 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
really about supporting Saudi
Arabia and repairing
the relationship.

30:41.940 --> 30:49.881 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, they understand that they're
in a hard
place because of the blowback
and the concerns

30:49.915 --> 30:54.886 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that the United States is being
tainted by
the support of the Saudi
Arabians in this

30:54.920 --> 30:56.722 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
conflict.

30:56.755 --> 30:59.357 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But do you -- is
it your sense
that the administration has
explained the

30:59.391 --> 31:01.993 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
conflict here, the contradiction
here?

31:02.027 --> 31:04.362 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
COL. DEREK HARVEY: No, not at
all.

31:04.396 --> 31:09.501 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is another war that is
forgotten. It's
on the back burner. It's, in
part, part of

31:09.534 --> 31:14.206 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
our larger C.T. strategy that
imploded almost
a year ago in Yemen.

31:14.239 --> 31:15.407 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Counterterrorism.

31:15.440 --> 31:17.743 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
COL. DEREK HARVEY: Yes, our
counterterrorism
strategy.

31:17.776 --> 31:22.848 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, unfortunately, since the
civil war expanded
and the Saudis became involved,
our ability

31:22.881 --> 31:29.287 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to go after al-Qaida and the
expanding Islamic
State elements in Yemen has been
hurt.

31:29.321 --> 31:34.893 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But it sounds as
if the prospects
for working this out are --
remain very difficult.

31:34.926 --> 31:37.963 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's a cease-fire and peace
talks, but
no assurances.

31:37.996 --> 31:41.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
COL. DEREK HARVEY: I think we're
just at the
beginning of that journey. The
talks that

31:41.967 --> 31:46.104 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are coming up in Kuwait City
mid-month are
a good step.

31:46.138 --> 31:50.842 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There has been some exchanges of
prisoners.
There's talk on both sides. But
we're a long

31:50.876 --> 31:55.347 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ways away from exhaustion on
both sides or
one side being able to impose
its will on

31:55.380 --> 32:00.652 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the other. So I think this
conflict is going
to rage on. And there's really,
you know,

32:00.685 --> 32:01.920 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
bleak prospects.

32:01.953 --> 32:05.791 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Colonel Derek
Harvey, we thank
you very much.

32:05.824 --> 32:14.199 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
COL. DEREK HARVEY: Thank you,
Judy.

32:14.232 --> 32:25.877 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Twenty-five years
ago this October,
University of Oklahoma law
Professor Anita

32:25.911 --> 32:32.551 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Hill changed Supreme Court
confirmation hearings
forever. Twenty million
households tuned in

32:32.584 --> 32:38.190 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to see her testify that her
former boss, nominee
Clarence Thomas, sexually
harassed her.

32:38.223 --> 32:43.795 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The hearings continued through
the weekend,
touching hot buttons of sex,
power and race.

32:43.829 --> 32:46.598 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Thomas called it a high-tech
lynching.

32:46.631 --> 32:51.970 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HBO Films retells the story in
"Confirmation,"
starring Kerry Washington and
Wendell Pierce

32:52.003 --> 32:53.738 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
as Thomas.

32:53.772 --> 32:59.644 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ACTOR: If what you say this man
said to you
occurred, why in God's name,
when he left

32:59.678 --> 33:07.519 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
his position of power or status
or authority
over you, why in God's name
would you ever

33:07.552 --> 33:10.121 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
speak to a man like that the
rest of your
life?

33:10.155 --> 33:17.395 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KERRY WASHINGTON, Actress:
That's a very good
question. And I am sure that I
cannot answer

33:17.429 --> 33:25.737 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it to your satisfaction. I have
suggested
that I was afraid of
retaliation. I was afraid

33:25.770 --> 33:29.007 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of damage to my professional
life.

33:29.040 --> 33:37.148 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I believed that -- you have to
understand
that this kind of response is
not atypical,

33:37.182 --> 33:46.091 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and I can't explain it. It takes
an expert
in psychology to explain how
that can happen.

33:46.124 --> 33:51.930 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But it can happen, because it
happened to
me.

33:51.963 --> 33:57.369 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Anita Hill, now a
professor of
law at Brandeis University,
joins me now.

33:57.402 --> 34:02.908 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You said you watched this film
about a week
ago. Did you hesitate at all to
relive that

34:02.941 --> 34:04.809 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
again?

34:04.843 --> 34:06.811 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANITA HILL, Professor of Law,
Brandeis University:
Well, I have relived it on other
occasions,

34:06.845 --> 34:09.180 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and so this wasn't the first
time.

34:09.214 --> 34:12.317 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There was a documentary a couple
of years
ago.

34:12.350 --> 34:13.451 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: It was called
"Anita."

34:13.485 --> 34:15.320 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ANITA HILL: It was called
"Anita."

34:15.353 --> 34:24.095 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's still hard, but I -- I
know it's
important, and it's something
that I was willing

34:24.129 --> 34:27.232 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to do, because I really wanted
to know how
HBO of going to tell the story.

34:27.265 --> 34:34.039 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: You know, you have
lived in this
your entire -- the past
quarter-of-a-century.

34:34.072 --> 34:39.945 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Many people are just coming new
to the story
or remember it vaguely. Do you
look back on

34:39.978 --> 34:41.579 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
it and think, I would do this
again?

34:41.613 --> 34:44.883 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ANITA HILL: I would do it again.

34:44.916 --> 34:48.954 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Many people do remember it
vaguely, but I
run into people all the time who
remember

34:48.987 --> 34:55.260 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it vividly. As a matter of fact,
when I was
on the flight here this morning
from Boston,

34:55.293 --> 34:58.296 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a woman -- I said, "Boy, you
really have a
good memory."

34:58.330 --> 35:01.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And she says: "I remember it so
well. It was
like it just happened."

35:01.099 --> 35:06.438 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: You accumulated
labels during
this process. You were either a
liar in some

35:06.471 --> 35:08.540 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
people's eyes or a truth-teller.

35:08.573 --> 35:10.976 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Do you worry that you will never
be able to
shed those labels?

35:11.009 --> 35:14.245 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ANITA HILL: I don't worry about
it. I just
keep living my life.

35:14.279 --> 35:17.048 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's been 25 years. There are
just people
who don't know the story.

35:17.082 --> 35:18.316 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: People who weren't
born.

35:18.350 --> 35:21.519 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ANITA HILL: People who weren't
born, don't
know the story.

35:21.553 --> 35:25.256 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think they're going to
find it really
interesting. In some ways, it is
going to

35:25.290 --> 35:29.127 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
seem like ancient history to
them, but I think,
in many ways, it is going to
seem just like

35:29.160 --> 35:34.199 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
today, because some of the
issues that were
raised, as you pointed out in
the introduction,

35:34.232 --> 35:36.201 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
are so contemporary. They
haven't gone away.

35:36.234 --> 35:40.171 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: I'm old enough to
have remembered
the hearings at the time. And I
was shocked

35:40.205 --> 35:47.846 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
then. I am shocked now, reliving
it and watching
the things that were said, the
different characters

35:47.879 --> 35:50.215 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that different senators and
others took on.

35:50.248 --> 35:52.384 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I wonder if it is surreal
for you, too.

35:52.417 --> 35:57.022 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ANITA HILL: It was surreal to
experience that.

35:57.055 --> 36:03.895 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, unfortunately, I hear from
women in particular,
but women and men, who come up
against this

36:03.928 --> 36:09.567 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
kind of power and this kind of
resistance
all the time. And,
unfortunately, they're

36:09.601 --> 36:14.406 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
getting some of the same kinds
of inaccurate
statements, some of the
fallacies, some of

36:14.439 --> 36:19.110 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the myths that were behind what
the senators
were doing are being repeated
over and over

36:19.144 --> 36:20.545 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
again.

36:20.578 --> 36:23.014 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Have you talked to
Kerry Washington
about her playing you?

36:23.048 --> 36:29.754 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANITA HILL: She and I spoke when
she was preparing
to play me. And she works very
hard to understand

36:29.788 --> 36:31.523 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the person.

36:31.556 --> 36:36.161 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I have a lot of respect for
that. I was
actually comforted by it and
thought, OK,

36:36.194 --> 36:41.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
well, if hard work is what it
takes and skill,
she -- she's going to pull it
off very nicely.

36:41.299 --> 36:45.737 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: And this movie
captures, you were
personally -- your character was
dragged through

36:45.770 --> 36:49.941 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the mud. I'm sure Clarence
Thomas would say
his was as well.

36:49.974 --> 36:53.945 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I wonder if you have spoken
with any of
the senators who were on that
committee since.

36:53.978 --> 36:55.547 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ANITA HILL: I have not spoken
with them.

36:55.580 --> 36:57.082 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Have they reached
out to you?

36:57.115 --> 37:00.585 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ANITA HILL: Arlen Specter did at
one point.

37:00.618 --> 37:06.057 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He suggested that we -- what he
said was,
"I was thinking we might be able
to work on

37:06.091 --> 37:07.859 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
something together."

37:07.892 --> 37:10.562 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But I just couldn't see that as
a possibility.

37:10.595 --> 37:16.734 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: How do young women
react to you
now? You're on a college campus.
College campuses

37:16.768 --> 37:21.406 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are hotbeds of debate for things
-- among
other things, sexual assault
cases now.

37:21.439 --> 37:26.611 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANITA HILL: Sexual harassment
and sexual assault
really is something that is on
the minds of

37:26.644 --> 37:28.480 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
young women today.

37:28.513 --> 37:33.885 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I do visit -- I'm on a college
campus. We're
grappling with those issues. I
visit colleges

37:33.918 --> 37:40.024 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
all over the country.
High-profile colleges
like Berkeley, U.C. Berkeley,
are grappling

37:40.058 --> 37:46.264 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with them, making decisions, in
some cases,
that are just wrongheaded
decisions about

37:46.297 --> 37:49.234 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
how to proceed with sexual
harassment claims.

37:49.267 --> 37:55.807 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are two that are out there
now, one
involving an administrator, the
other involving

37:55.840 --> 38:03.648 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a high-profile faculty member.
And so these
issues are very present. And I
have to credit

38:03.681 --> 38:08.353 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
some very, very brave young
women and men
for taking this on, on college
campuses.

38:08.386 --> 38:12.724 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: One of the things
that also crossed
my mind while I was watching
this is whether

38:12.757 --> 38:18.329 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
you could have survived, whether
this, any
of this set of events could have
unfolded

38:18.363 --> 38:25.470 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in our current age in a time of
instantaneous
social media and Twitter and
instant judgment?

38:25.503 --> 38:31.843 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANITA HILL: I don't upon how any
of -- how
this would unfold today in this
environment.

38:31.876 --> 38:37.015 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I can tell you a funny
story. One of the
things that I tell to people is,
I have a

38:37.048 --> 38:44.222 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
collection of faxes that I got.
Well, we wouldn't
have faxes. We didn't even have
e-mail so

38:44.255 --> 38:51.996 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
much. Western Union, I think,
fell under the
crunch of the telegrams that
were coming.

38:52.030 --> 38:58.903 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It would be quite different
today. But I don't
-- I think that the issues are
such that it

38:58.937 --> 39:04.342 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
wouldn't go away. It wouldn't be
instant.
I think it would be different.
The forums

39:04.375 --> 39:09.714 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for discussing it would be
different, but
the issue wouldn't disappear
just because

39:09.747 --> 39:11.549 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
we live in an instant society.

39:11.583 --> 39:17.855 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: When -- at one point
in the film,
the character, and presumably
you, said, this

39:17.889 --> 39:23.561 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
was a mistake. Do you still
think it was a
mistake? And, if not what,
changed your mind?

39:23.595 --> 39:29.601 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
ANITA HILL: I think the
character -- my words
aren't always exactly what the
characters

39:29.634 --> 39:30.802 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
are saying.

39:30.835 --> 39:32.170 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, that's the thing about
fictional
adaptations.

39:32.203 --> 39:33.137 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: Right.

39:33.171 --> 39:36.674 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ANITA HILL: I don't think it was
a mistake.

39:36.708 --> 39:42.413 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think it was something that
was meant to
happen, actually. I had
something to say.

39:42.447 --> 39:46.718 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I had an experience to share
that went to
the fitness of an individual who
was going

39:46.751 --> 39:52.757 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to be sitting on a Supreme Court
with a lifetime
appointment. It was important,
not only to

39:52.790 --> 39:59.831 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
the integrity of this
individual, but also
to the integrity of the court
itself.

39:59.864 --> 40:06.337 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And as a member of the bar, as a
citizen,
I had a right to come forward
and to testify.

40:06.371 --> 40:15.213 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I don't think we -- that is ever
a mistake.
And I really wouldn't do it
differently today.

40:15.246 --> 40:19.417 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: Anita Hill,
professor of law at
Brandeis University, thank you
very much.

40:19.450 --> 40:20.919 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ANITA HILL: Thank you.

