suffocating.

46:52.243 --> 46:56.781 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN (through translator): It's
impossible
to breathe in them. We cannot
breathe when

46:56.814 --> 46:58.616 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
we wear them.

46:58.649 --> 47:02.086 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: A few mines
now do provide
for wet drilling and require
workers to wear

47:02.119 --> 47:07.792 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
