47:24.308 --> 47:29.346 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: GRAVIS,
which is funded
by charitable donations from
abroad and some

47:29.380 --> 47:34.752 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Indian government grants, also
helps affected
miners navigate the daunting
government bureaucracy.

47:34.785 --> 47:39.690 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. PRAKASH TYAGI: There is a
lot of paperwork.
There is a lot of delay. But we
try to make

47:39.724 --> 47:44.995 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
sure that these people who are
illiterate
and less capable go through
those hurdles.

47:45.029 --> 47:50.835 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: The
compensation, about
1,700 U.S. dollars for living
victims, $3,000

47:50.868 --> 47:56.474 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for their survivors, provides
some debt relief,
more money to travel and perhaps
find new

47:56.507 --> 47:58.275 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
work.

47:58.309 --> 48:02.213 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But Tyagi says his and a few
other groups
meet only a small fraction of
the need, while

48:02.246 --> 48:08.652 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
he says thousands of silicosis
victims scattered
across this remote region suffer
and die each

48:08.686 --> 48:11.255 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
